  "prompt": "How can I open DWG files in Adobe Illustrator?",
  "response": "To open DWG files in Adobe Illustrator, you have a few options:\n\n1. Direct Method (Illustrator CC):\n- Open Illustrator\n- Go to File > Open\n- Select your DWG file\n- Illustrator should import the file directly\n\n2. Alternative Methods:\n- Use Autodesk DWG Converter to convert DWG to a compatible format like PDF or AI\n- Use AutoCAD to export the DWG as a PDF or AI file\n- Use third-party conversion software like Convertio or CloudConvert\n\n3. Recommended Workflow:\n- Open the file in AutoCAD first\n- Export/Save As a format compatible with Illustrator (PDF, AI)\n- Open the converted file in Illustrator\n\n4. Plugin Options:\n- Some plugins like CADtools can enhance DWG import capabilities in Illustrator\n\n5. Tips:\n- Ensure you have the latest version of Illustrator\n- Check file compatibility and complex drawing elements\n- Some complex CAD drawings might require manual cleanup after import\n\nIf you're having persistent issues, consider using specialized CAD conversion software or consulting with a CAD professional.",
